=====

> "Think of your child, then, not as dead, but as living; not as a flower that has withered, but as one that is transplanted, and touched by a Divine hand, is blooming in richer colors and sweeter shades than those of earth." is a quotation from Richard Hooker in //Dictionary of Burning Words of Brilliant Writers,// 1895 in the public domain.

